==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-sponge.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''sponge''' (countable and uncountable; plural: [[sponges]]) 
{{wikipedia}}
# (''countable'') Any of various [[marine]] [[invertebrate]]s, mostly of the phylum ''[[Porifera]]'' that have a [[porous]] [[skeleton]] often of [[silica]]
# (''uncountable'') A material consisting mostly of air bubbles, used to wash dishes or the body
# (''countable'') A light [[cake]] or [[steamed pudding]]
# (''slang'') A person who takes advantage of the generosity of others.

===Verb===
'''sponging''' 
# (''slang'') to beg
#*'''1883:''' [[w:Robert Louis Stevenson|Robert Louis Stevenson]], ''[[w:Treasure Island|Treasure Island]]''
#*: I'm to be a poor, crawling beggar, '''sponging''' for rum, when I might be rolling in a coach!

